\begin{align*}
\frac{21}{2^2 \cdot 5^7} &= \frac{21}{4 \cdot 5^5} \\
&= \frac{21}{20} \\
&= \frac{1}{2} + \frac{1}{20} \\
&= \frac{1}{2} + 0.05 \\
&= \boxed{\frac{1}{2} + 0.05}
\end{align*}
Therefore, the answer is $\frac{1}{2} + 0.05$.

