\sqrt{2}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} + \sqrt{3} + \frac{1}{\sqrt{3}} &= \sqrt{2}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}} \\
&= \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{6}}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{6}} \\
&= \frac{1}{\sqrt{6}}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{6}}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{6}}+\frac{1}{\sqrt{6}} \\
&= \frac{4}{\sqrt{6}}
\end{align*}
Therefore, we have:
\begin{align*}
\dfrac{a\sqrt{2} + b\sqrt{3}}{c} &= \dfrac{4}{\sqrt{6}} \\
a\sqrt{2} + b\sqrt{3} &= 4\sqrt{6} \\
a\sqrt{2} &= 4\sqrt{6}-\sqrt{6} \\
a &= 3
\end{align*}
\begin{align*}
a\sqrt{2} + b\sqrt{3} &= 4\sqrt{6}-\sqrt{6} \\
3\sqrt{2} + b\sqrt{3} &= 3\sqrt{6} \\
b\sqrt{3} &= 3\sqrt{6}-\sqrt{6} \\
b &= 2
\end{align*}
\begin{align*}
a\sqrt{2} + b\sqrt{3} &= 3\sqrt{2}+2\sqrt{3} \\
c &= 1
\end{align*}
Therefore, $a+b+c = 3+2+1 = \boxed{6}$.

