Let \[f(n) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
\lfloor n \rfloor & \text{ if }n \geq 4, \\
\lceil n \rceil & \text{ if } n < 4.
\end{array}
\right.\]Find $f\left(\frac{\pi}{3}\right) + f(\sqrt{45}) + f(8^{2/3})$.

output:
Let's evaluate each term separately:

$$\begin{aligned}
f\left(\frac{\pi}{3}\right) &= \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
\lfloor \frac{\pi}{3} \rfloor & \text{ if } \frac{\pi}{3} \geq 4, \\
\lceil \frac{\pi}{3} \rceil & \text{ if } \frac{\pi}{3} < 4.
\end{array}
\right. \\
&= \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
3 & \text{ if } \frac{\pi}{3} \geq 4, \\
2 & \text{ if } \frac{\pi}{3} < 4.
\end{array}
\right. \\
&= 2.
\end{aligned}$$

$$\begin{aligned}
f(\sqrt{45}) &= \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
\lfloor \sqrt{45} \rfloor & \text{ if } \sqrt{45} \geq 4, \\
\lceil \sqrt{45} \rceil & \text{ if } \sqrt{45} < 4.
\end{array}
\right. \\
&= \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
3 & \text{ if } \sqrt{45} \geq 4, \\
2 & \text{ if } \sqrt{45} < 4.
\end{array}
\right. \\
&= 2.
\end{aligned}$$

$$\begin{aligned}
f(8^{2/3}) &= \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
\lfloor 8^{2/3} \rfloor & \text{ if } 8^{2/3} \geq 4, \\
\lceil 8^{2/3} \rceil & \text{ if } 8^{2/3} < 4.
\end{array}
\right. \\
&= \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
3 & \text{ if } 8^{2/3} \geq 4, \\
2 & \text{ if } 8^{2/3} < 4.
\end{array}
\right. \\
&= 2.
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore,

$$\boxed{2 + 2 + 2 = 6}.$$

